 A couple years ago when 10nm was slipping, Intel said the lessons it&#39;ll learn in pushing ahead with 10nm despite setbacks would be useful for pushing 7nm afterward. However, Intel still hasn&#39;t fully sorted 10nm out and I&#39;m guessing that some of the lessons learned don&#39;t port over to 7nm quite as well as Intel hoped they would.  Looks like Intel may not have much for people to get excited about until 2022.
